There is currently no way to view the historical contents of a page via the remote interface.  It would be nice if the getPageByVersion service were exposed on the SOAP and XMLRPC interfaces.  This will allow remote clients to create visual diffs of two versions like is currently done in the web UI.

Attached is a patch that adds a new service getPageByVersion to both the XMRPC and SOAP interfaces.  I was unable to test it as I couldn't get Confluence to run on my machine (possibly a Java6 issue)

